infoparam.name: UML Note
infoparam.value:
The system adressed by the model was first described by Prof. Ludovic Apvrille in 2007. The solution posted on soc.eurecom.fr/UMLEmb/exams.html used TTool and TAU G2, using the TURTLE and UML/SDL profiles, respectively. The model included in this file exclusively uses the SysML/AVATAR syntax and TTool.
Last Update: July 02, 2018.
Authors Pierre de Saqui-Sannes pdss@isae-supaero.fr
Ludovic Apvrille ludovic.apvrille@telecom-paristech.fr
Cooperation with ISAE-CNAM students (2017-2018).

Line.value: The system adressed by the model was first described by Prof. Ludovic Apvrille in 2007.
The solution posted on soc.eurecom.fr/UMLEmb/exams.html used TTool and TAU G2,
using the TURTLE and UML/SDL profiles, respectively.
The model included in this file exclusively uses the SysML/AVATAR syntax and TTool.

textline.data: The model does not describe the shutdown procedure.
The model does not describe the set up procedure.
The system is supposed to be correctly initialized.
The model does not address battery management.
The model does not address maintenance.
None of the devices connected to the system will ever fail.
